2025-12-12 | Plus One to a Large Integer Represented as Digits

Question
Given an integer array digits representing a large number,  
increment the number by one and return the resulting array of digits.

Approach
1.	Start from the **last digit** (least significant digit).
2.	Add 1 to the current digit.
3.	If the digit becomes 10:
	-	Set it to 0.
	-	Carry 1 to the next digit on the left.
4.	Continue moving left while there is a carry.
5.	If all digits were 9 and a carry remains at the end:
	-	Insert 1 at the beginning of the array.
6.	Time Complexity: O(n).  
   Space Complexity: O(1) extra (output array excluded).

Solution
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> plusOne(vector<int>& digits) {
        int n = digits.size();

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (digits[i] < 9) {
                digits[i]++;
                return digits;
            }
            digits[i] = 0;
        }

        // If all digits were 9
        digits.insert(digits.begin(), 1);
        return digits;
    }
};
